  m_text: is the most widely used temperature scale in the world. It is based on
    both the freezing and boiling points of water under 1 atm of air pressure, and
    it is the easiest to remember. It scales from zero (0) for the freezing point
    of water, up to a hundred (100) for boiling point of water. It is named after
    Anders Celsius.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
